! PaintTool I/O Auto Configurator Data File (PaDiagDb.dt)
! This data file is used to Automatically configure the PaintTool Diagnostic
! schedules based on PaintTool option configurations.  This data
! file is a TAB-delimited file that can be edited with Microsoft
! Excel, Microsoft NotePad, Microsoft WordPad, or any editor that does
! not remove the TAB-delimited characters from this Database.
! Note: Microsoft Excel inserts bogus characters for two-dimensioal
! arrays, therefore, it is not a recommended editor!
! (example ins_to_par[1,1] will change to ""ins_to_par[1,1]"" resulting
! in an error when this file is processed!)
! Note: Comment lines may be inserted any place in this data file,
! either inside a TOKEN or outside outside of a TOKEN but both must
! start with the character (!) only!!!  This data file processes
! three tokens (VAR) to setup variables for the Profibus I/O option, the
! following syntax is required:
! VAR  U.P.#1  U.V.#1  U.C.#1  U.P.#2  U.V.#2  U.C.#2  I.P.  I.V.								
! where:								
!   VAR - Instructs I/O Auto Configurator to assign Variable	
!	U.P.#1(User Program #1) - User program #1 name (KAREL or *SYSTEM*)
!	U.V.#1(User Variable #1) - User variable #1 name
!	U.C.#1(User Value #1) - User value #1 (This token is processed if
!                           variable #1 value = R-J3 variable)	
!	U.P.#2(User Program #2) - User program #2 name (KAREL or *SYSTEM*)
!	U.V.#2(User Variable #2) - User variable #2 name
!	U.C.#2(User Value #2) - User value #2 (This token is processed if
!                           variable #2 value = R-J3 variable)	
!	I.P.(Integer Program) - Integer program name (KAREL or *SYSTEM*)
!	I.V.(Integer Variable) - Integer variable name (PaintTool default
!                            is the following:	
!	
!                            Applicator Types [PAVROPTN]which_gun,	
!                            user selects this at Controlled Start Menu)	
!   where:	
!     Supported Applicator Types (which_gun):										
!       Gun						[PAVROPTN]which_gun = 1
!       Bell(306)					[PAVROPTN]which_gun = 2
!       Bell(607)					[PAVROPTN]which_gun = 3
!       VersaBell					[PAVROPTN]which_gun = 4
!       ServoBell					[PAVROPTN]which_gun = 5
!										       
!										
! *****NOTE:*****										
!	
! The contents between the VAR TOKEN and the STOPSECTION may contain	
! only the following syntax, either a comment line (!) or a variable	
! assignment line as described below:	
!	
! User Integer  Data Type  Program  Variable  Value	
! where:	
!  User Integer	This is the User Integer field that contains a
!               specified value used to compare against the Integer	
!               Variable defined in the VAR TOKEN.  PaintTool defaults	
!               this Integer Variable to [PAVROPTN]which_gun with the	
!               following configurations:	
!  where:	
!    0 -	Any Applicator Type
!    1 -	Gun
!    2 -	Bell(306)	
!    3 -	Bell(607)	
!    4 -	VersaBell
!    5 -	ServoBell
!		       
!  Data Type	This is the Data Type field with the following types	
!               supported:		
!  where:		
!    BOOLEAN	Can specify 0, 1, FALSE, or TRUE	
!    BYTE		Whole numbers from 1 to 255
!    SHORT		Whole numbers from 1 to 32767
!    INTEGER	        Whole numbers from -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647	
!    REAL		Fraction numbers from 10xy-38 to 10xy38
!    STRING		Character expressions from 1 to 80 characters
!		
!  Program	This is the Program name field which must contain a
!               valid KAREL program name loaded onto the controller or		
!               *SYSTEM*.		
!		
!  Variable		This is the Variable name field which must contain a
!               valid KAREL program variable loaded onto the controller		
!               or *SYSTEM*.		
!		
!  Value		This is the Value field which is the value that the
!               above specified variable will be assigned.		
!		
!  NOTE: The following constants are defined in PAVROPPR.EDD to represent the array index		
!        element into the new [PAVROPTN]byOptn[1].byOp[MAX_OPS] OF BYTE data type to conserve memory		
!        for boolean data type operations in PaintTool!		
!  ConvSyncOpt  = 1;		
!  job_que_rep  = 2;		
!  job_ent_tp   = 3;		
!  job_strt_sg  = 4;		
!  job_clr_que  = 5;		
!  job_in_que   = 6;
!  pushout_req  = 7;
!  pamnent_clr  = 8;
!  rob_cc_use   = 9;
!  rob_accu_use = 10;
!  rob_dq_set   = 11;
!  rob_cc_set   = 12;
!  rob_last_use = 13;
!  rob_auto_out = 14;
!  CPXType = 15 (0 = Non-P-500, 
!                1 = CPX-MPA-1K/IC, 
!                2 = CPX-MPA-2K, 
!                3 = CPX-MPA-Simple2K)
!  rob_ac_use   = 16;
!  rob_ac_set   = 17;
!  rob_ac2_use  = 18;
!  rob_ln_use   = 19;
!  rob_ln_set   = 20;
!  rob_rl_use   = 21;
!  rob_rl_set   = 22;
!  rob_jog_pn   = 23;
!  AutoTCPUpd   = 24;
!  rob_eip_use  = 25;
!  rob_canc_use = 26;
